<form version="1.1" theme="dark" script="carbide_inline_edit.js" stylesheet="carbide.css">
    <label>Manage assets</label>
    <description>Per-host metadata that Carbide joins to the live status macro so alerts and dashboards carry asset context (criticality, owner, business unit). Works without ES; populate manually below, or enable the ES asset_lookup_by_str sync saved search if you have ES. Empty collection = no enrichment, no errors.</description>

    <fieldset submitButton="false" autoRun="true">
        <input type="text" token="asset_search_tok" searchWhenChanged="true">
            <label>Search host (contains)</label>
            <default></default>
        </input>
        <input type="dropdown" token="asset_crit_tok" searchWhenChanged="true">
            <label>Criticality</label>
            <choice value="*">All</choice>
            <choice value="critical">critical</choice>
            <choice value="high">high</choice>
            <choice value="medium">medium</choice>
            <choice value="low">low</choice>
            <default>*</default>
        </input>
    </fieldset>

    <row>
        <panel>
            <html>
                <div class="carbide-toolbar">
                    <div class="carbide-toolbar-info">
                        <strong>How this is used:</strong> the host status macro does
                        <code>| lookup carbide_assets_lookup host OUTPUTNEW criticality AS asset_criticality, owner AS asset_owner, business_unit AS asset_bu</code>.
                        Asset fields appear on the Manage entities view (when "Show details" is on)
                        and in the email + notable alert templates.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </html>
        </panel>
    </row>

    <row>
        <panel>
            <title>Asset overrides</title>
            <table id="carbide_assets_table"
                   data-carbide-collection="carbide_assets"
                   data-carbide-editable="host,criticality,owner,business_unit,notes,source"
                   data-carbide-options-criticality="low,medium,high,critical"
                   data-carbide-label-host="Host"
                   data-carbide-label-criticality="Criticality"
                   data-carbide-label-owner="Owner"
                   data-carbide-label-business_unit="Business unit"
                   data-carbide-label-source="Source (manual|es_asset_sync)">
                <search>
                    <query>
                        | inputlookup carbide_assets_lookup
                        | search criticality="$asset_crit_tok$"
                        | where like(lower(coalesce(host,"")), lower("%$asset_search_tok$%"))
                        | sort + host
                        | eval kv_key = _key
                        | table kv_key, host, criticality, owner, business_unit, source, notes
                    </query>
                    </search>
                <option name="drilldown">none</option>
                <option name="count">100</option>
                <format type="color" field="criticality">
                    <colorPalette type="map">{"low":#888888,"medium":#f8be34,"high":#dc4e41,"critical":#9b1d1d}</colorPalette>
                </format>
            </table>
        </panel>
    </row>

    <row>
        <panel>
            <title>Add asset</title>
            <html>
                <div class="carbide-form">
                    <label>Host <input type="text" id="carbide_new_asset_host" placeholder="e.g. web01.prod" /></label>
                    <label>Criticality
                        <select id="carbide_new_asset_criticality">
                            <option value="low">low</option>
                            <option value="medium" selected="selected">medium</option>
                            <option value="high">high</option>
                            <option value="critical">critical</option>
                        </select>
                    </label>
                    <label>Owner <input type="text" id="carbide_new_asset_owner" placeholder="owner@example.com" /></label>
                    <label>Business unit <input type="text" id="carbide_new_asset_bu" placeholder="payments" /></label>
                    <label>Notes <input type="text" id="carbide_new_asset_notes" placeholder="optional"/></label>
                    <button id="carbide_add_asset"
                            class="btn btn-primary"
                            data-carbide-collection="carbide_assets"
                            data-carbide-target="carbide_assets_table">Add asset</button>
                </div>
            </html>
        </panel>
    </row>

    <row>
        <panel>
            <title>Sync from Splunk Enterprise Security (optional)</title>
            <html>
                <p style="color:#b8bec5;">
                  If ES is installed and <code>asset_lookup_by_str</code> is populated,
                  enable the <em>Carbide - Sync ES asset_lookup_by_str to carbide_assets</em>
                  saved search in Settings &#8250; Searches. It runs nightly at 03:17 and
                  upserts the ES asset list into this collection so the Carbide host status
                  macro can enrich every live status with criticality / owner / business unit.
                </p>
                <p style="color:#7a8590;font-size:12px;">
                  Without ES, populate this table manually with the rows that matter to you.
                  Carbide treats the lookup as best-effort &#8212; an empty table is a valid state.
                </p>
            </html>
        </panel>
    </row>

    <row>
        <panel>
            <title>Delete asset</title>
            <html>
                <p style="color:#b8bec5;font-size:13px;">Paste an asset row's <code>kv_key</code> to remove it.</p>
                <div class="carbide-delete-row">
                    <input type="text" id="carbide_delete_key_assets" placeholder="kv_key to remove"
                           data-carbide-collection="carbide_assets"
                           data-carbide-delete-target="carbide_assets_table" />
                    <button id="carbide_delete_button_assets" class="btn btn-danger">Delete asset</button>
                </div>
            </html>
        </panel>
    </row>
</form>
